                                            <content type="html">
                            &lt;p&gt;This is great idea. Thanks for that!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What about retrospective between sessions ? &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;cite&gt;Valdis Pornieks said:&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote cite=&quot;http://coderetreat.org/forum/topics/question-on-final-retrospective?groupUrl=facilitators&amp;amp;#6456126Comment22167&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;xg_user_generated&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Depending on the crowd in the last session I usually try to introduce a different variation of the problem or different approach to looking at it. That leaves the participants thinking. Also in the final retrospection you can ask additional questions on the general organisation and experience of the coderetreat, so that you can improve your process too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
